properties.headline: Flood Warning issued January 31 at 3:35PM PST until February 1 at 6:28AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in Seattle has issued a flood warning
for the following rivers in Washington...

Skykomish River Near Gold Bar affecting Snohomish County
Snoqualmie River Near Snoqualmie Falls affecting King County
Snoqualmie River Near Carnation affecting King County


Heavy rain overnight with a good punch this morning,and again
tonight, with the addition of a little lower elevation snow melt,
will drive these rivers above flood stage.

The National Weather Service in Seattle has issued a

* Flood Warning for
The Skykomish River Near Gold Bar
* until Saturday morning.
* At  2:30 PM Friday the stage was 14.2 feet.
* Flood stage is 15.0 feet.
* Minor flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river will rise above flood stage around 4 PM Friday
and crest near 15.3 feet around 4 PM Friday. The river will fall
below flood stage this evening.
* Impact...At 15.0 feet, the Skykomish River will cause minor flooding
of low pasture lands and low lying roads...including Index-Galena
Rd and Tualco Loop Rd.  A stage of 15 feet on the Skykomish River
corresponds to a Phase 2 in the Snohomish County flood program.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.
